    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/1.-reconnaissance/credential-in-source-code/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/1.-reconnaissance/credential-in-source-code/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;trufflehog&#34;&gt;Trufflehog&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#trufflehog&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/trufflesecurity/trufflehog&#34;&gt;Github Page&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This tool will find sensitive credentials exposed in the repo&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;trufflehog github --repo https://github.com/username/repo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/1.-reconnaissance/port-scan/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/1.-reconnaissance/port-scan/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;full-tcp-scan&#34;&gt;Full TCP scan&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#full-tcp-scan&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;rustscan&#34;&gt;RustScan&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#rustscan&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I usually use rustscan for pure port scan since it will be faster and not much syntax. I saved it in my &lt;code&gt;PATH&lt;/code&gt; to call it easier, but you do you&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/bee-san/RustScan&#34;&gt;Github Repo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Download and extract binary&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;wget https://github.com/bee-san/RustScan/releases/download/2.4.1/x86_64-linux-rustscan.tar.gz.zip&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;unzip x86_64-linux-rustscan.tar.gz.zip&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;tar -xzvf x86_64-linux-rustscan.tar.gz&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Quick all ports tcp scan.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;./rustscan -a 10.10.10.10,10.10.10.20 -g&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;nmap&#34;&gt;Nmap&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#nmap&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;nmap -sS -p- --min-rate&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;1000&lt;/span&gt; -T4 $target --max-retries &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt; | grep &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;^[0-9]&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; | cut -d &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;/&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; -f &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; | tr &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;\n&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;,&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; | sed s/,$//&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;script-scan&#34;&gt;Script scan&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#script-scan&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I do this as my &amp;ldquo;default&amp;rdquo; scan&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
